All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Agent
This class represents an agent in the EE364 project.
Call
The Call class represents a simulated call in a call center.
Call.CallState
Enum representing the possible states of a phone call.
CallCenter
Represents a simulated call center with agents, call handling, and availability tracking.
CanCall
The CanCall interface represents entities that have the ability to make calls.
Csv
The Csv class provides utility methods for reading and writing CSV files using objects that implement the HasData interface.
Customer
This class represents a customer in the simulation.
Customer.CustomerState
This enum represents the possible states that a customer can be in.
Department
Represents a department implementing the HasData interface.
DialogeBox
The DialogeBox class represents a window displaying a dialogue associated with a call.
HasData
The HasData interface defines a contract for classes that represent data.
HeapSizeChecker
This class is used to keep track of the memory usage of the program.
InvalidIdException
Exception class for handling invalid IDs.
InvalidPhoneNumberException
Exception class for handling invalid phone numbers.
InvalidRatioValueException
Exception class for handling invalid ratio values.
MainFx
Main class for the JavaFX application.
MainSceneController
The MainSceneController class manages the GUI of the application.
NoDataException
Custom exception indicating that no data is available.
Person
The Person class represents an entity with a name and a tag.
Problem
The Problem class represents an issue or scenario within a department, encapsulating information about the problem, its associated department, and a list of solutions.
Ratio
The Ratio class represents a ratio value between 0 and 1.
Simulated
An interface for objects that can be stepped through simulation.
Solution
The ConversationData class encapsulates data related to conversations between customers and agents in a simulated environment.
Timekeeper
The TimeManager class manages time-related properties for simulation.
Utilities
This class provides various utility functions for the project.
Vars
This class contains all the static variables used throughout the project.
Vars.DataClasses
The DataClasses class provides constants for various data types used in the application.
Zip
The Zip class provides utility methods for extracting and compressing ZIP files.
